 Given these limitations, a number of scholars have introduced novel empirical
 approaches to explore different aspects of elite politics.
 Such studies are particularly developed in the studies of the CCP elite,
 and they largely fall into two separate lines of inquiries: (1) identifying
 key actors (i.e., the positional approach) and (2) exploring their relations
 (i.e., the relational approach).
\end_layout

